Looking forward for memories to come :)!

replies.body:
You're welcome:)), a blast to work with you!

If you want me to be completely honest, no. Since the first day we met on teamspeak you've been munch friend and it really means a lot we're still talking. I've seen you grow from a junior mod and the fact you've surpassed me in ranks means nothing, you don't brag but include me in stuff others don't. You give me chances to show my leadership, and thank you. You're a great person, player and staff member and you're going to go places in life, trust me. Keep doing what you're doing because you've got a pretty good rythum going:).

Hm, probably Drops of Jupiter by Train or If I had a million dollars by the bare naked ladies.

replies.body: Back then, did you see yourself being/still being a Moderator and a Referee? Or did you even see yourself still playing this server?
replies.body_tagged: Back then, did you see yourself being/still being a Moderator and a Referee? Or did you even see yourself still playing this server?

replies.body:
Back then, did you see yourself being/still being a Moderator and a Referee? Or did you even see yourself still playing this server?

To be honest, I wasn't very sure about still being a moderator but as long as tournament were being ran I knew I'd stick as referee. The community is what kept me here, and when some of my older friend left [Grape, Jess, Liz etc.] and I thought I was going to join them, and leave. Instead I found new friends and here I am today. I'd play on this server probably till it only has 5 or so players.
